e budgeting requires synchronizing efforts across different departments and management levels. This ensures that everyone is aware of the overall plan and works towards common goals.\"", "\"COMMUNICATION\":\"Communication in participative budgeting involves sharing the budget plan across all levels of management. Effective communication ensures that everyone understands the plan and any changes made during the budgeting process.\"", "\"SYSTEM OF CONTROL\":\"A system of control in budgeting involves comparing actual results to budgeted figures and investigating any differences. This process is crucial for maintaining effective control over organizational activities.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\":\"Performance evaluation in participative budgeting involves appraising managers by comparing their actual results to the budgeted results. This method is effective if the participation is genuine and free from budgetary slack.\"", "\"TIMANA CO\":\"Timana Co manufactures small-panel display screens for various consumer electronic products. The company faces challenges in a competitive industry with short product life cycles and pricing pressures. The finance director has proposed shifting from incremental budgeting to a rolling budget approach to better adapt to market changes.\"", "\"DIRECT MATERIAL\":\"DIRECT MATERIAL\" refers to the raw materials and components that are directly used in the manufacturing of a product. It is considered a variable cost that increases by 3% every quarter to reflect the increase in sales volume.", "\"SALES VOLUME GROWTH ASSUMPTION\":\"The assumption that sales volume would grow at the same fixed compound rate every quarter.\"", "\"VARIABLE COSTS ASSUMPTION\":\"The assumption that direct material and direct labour are wholly variable costs.\"", "\"FIXED PRODUCTION OVERHEADS ASSUMPTION\":\"The assumption that fixed production overheads would increase by $10,000 from Q3 onwards due to extra maintenance.\"", "\"ADMINISTRATION COSTS ASSUMPTION\":\"The assumption that administration costs would increase by 3% in Q3 to account for an increase in the rent for the building.\"", "\"SALES MANAGER'S COMMENT\":\"The sales manager's comment that he had to reduce selling prices to boost demand as the market became more competitive.\"", "\"PRODUCTION MANAGER'S COMMENT\":\"The production manager's comment that the direct labour cost was higher due to an increase in the minimum wage and that there will be a one-off increase of $5,000 in Q3 for additional training required under health and safety legislation.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}